| Check                                         | What data is used                                                   | How the LLM evaluates it                                                                                                                                                        |
| --------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **1. Clarity of explanation**                 | compliance_assessment, regulatory_information                       | The model reads the commentary and checks whether it clearly explains how the requirement is addressed. It looks for vague wording, missing explanation, or unclear statements. |
| **2. Completeness of commentary**             | compliance_assessment, compliance_status                            | The model checks whether the commentary alone explains why the status is given. It verifies that the conclusion can be understood without needing other entries.                |
| **3. Support for conclusion**                 | compliance_assessment, evidence, compliance_status                  | The model checks whether the commentary mentions supporting documents or references, and whether those references logically support the status assigned.                        |
| **4. Reference traceability**                 | evidence, compliance_assessment                                     | The model checks whether the reference is specific enough to locate the document (for example section, clause, date, version). Generic references are marked as weak.           |
| **5. Follow-up clarity (non-compliant only)** | compliance_status, return_to_compliance_plan, compliance_assessment | If the status is non-compliant or partial, the model checks whether the return-to-compliance plan clearly explains what action will be taken and how the gap will be resolved.  |
